  "rationale": "Conservatively adapt the selected crop-aware ViT to expert-annotated, real smallholder field images. The new source is split by duplicate group, the v1 test rows are byte-equivalent and immutable, and calibration gives each validation source equal total weight so near-clean lab sources cannot dominate field confidence.",
  "test_disclosure": "The frozen test was observed for prior candidates and exposed domain shift. This run was specified from the prior gate failures plus new disjoint training/validation data. No frozen-test image, label, logit, threshold, or duplicate is used for training, checkpoint selection, temperature fitting, or hierarchy fitting.",
  "models": [
